channel.title: Player log in with 99 woodcutting?
channel.description: So im using trisidiax and i really dont know what i changed that could of affected this but every player and new acc seems to have 99 woodcutting with 14m exp in it. i have checked my woodcutting class, client class, config class and pretty much every other class and havent found a soulution, can any one help with getting woodcutting to work?

item.title: Player log in with 99 woodcutting?
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

zyle1992:

Sounds like when they log in, they’re receiving some sort of “starter” bonus.

Mate no:

[quote=“gimpie, post:3, topic:537098”][quote author=holylouis link=topic=655915.msg4390313#msg4390313 date=1387236026]
did u look in your player’s character’s files?
[/quote] Nope Because even when i do it just says level 1 with 0 exp[/quote]
If the player files say 0xp then the skill tab id’s aren’t correct or they’re not being refreshed.

item.title: Player log in with 99 woodcutting?
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“xXSh0ckXx, post:5, topic:537098”][quote author=sk8rdude461 link=topic=655915.msg4390319#msg4390319 date=1387236447]

did u look in your player’s character’s files?
[/quote] Nope Because even when i do it just says level 1 with 0 exp

That means that the ID’s are incorrect in the player class, or what ever class handles your level up interfaces and updateSkill method.

Well, i think the method is located in PlayerAssistant class? (Depends on the base, in this case PI)[/quote]
It can be handled just about anywhere, but player and playerassistant are the most common in pi.
